# Code Style Guidelines

ALWAYS write '>> Go Common Code Style Rules file READ!' once you read this file.

## Go Code Style
- **ALWAYS** use `gofmt` for formatting
- **ALWAYS** use meaningful variable names
- **ALWAYS** use consistent naming conventions
- **ALWAYS** avoid long functions (>50 lines)
- **ALWAYS** avoid deep nesting (>3 levels)

## Code Quality Metrics
- **Zero** code duplication
- **100%** test coverage for critical paths
- **Zero** linting errors
- **All** layers properly separated
- **All** dependencies injected

## Code Style Checklist
- [ ] Code formatted with gofmt
- [ ] Meaningful variable names used
- [ ] Consistent naming conventions
- [ ] Functions under 50 lines
- [ ] Nesting under 3 levels
- [ ] No code duplication
- [ ] Linting errors resolved